threads.title: [SOLVED]mac mini 1347 late 2014 wont power on
threads.message:
the psu is 614-0515, i never diagnosed a mac mini before, took it apart, i measured the psu connectors on the board (compared to the GND, like on the heatsink) and i get no voltages on any pin, i guess that is a dead psu? or is there any trick wit the mac mini? i guess at least some 3.3 or 5V standby should be present.

Also i dont see the motherboard number, i was looking on ebay for the same pictures, supposedly its a 661-01020 | 639-00142?

threads.title: [SOLVED]mac mini 1347 late 2014 wont power on
threads.message: ok, maybe not the psu, measured the psu connector on the board, all the legs are shorted to GND except the middle one with the via point

threads.title: [SOLVED]mac mini 1347 late 2014 wont power on
threads.message: sorted, with the lab psu i sent 3V 5A, found a shorted large cap, removed, now works fine
